    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`height` option of the cmd window is ignored when entering command-line mode with `:`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- Enable UI2 with all windows clamped to 0.5:\n  ```lua\n  require('vim._core.ui2').enable {\n    enabled = true,\n    msg = {\n      targets = 'cmd',\n      cmd = {\n        height = 0.5,\n      },\n      dialog = {\n        height = 0.5,\n      },\n      msg = {\n        height = 0.5,\n      },\n      pager = {\n        height = 0.5,\n      },\n    },\n  }\n  ```\n- `:hi`\n- `:`\n- Output is unclamped:\n\n  <img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b7b6e514-d19d-4064-ba6b-a6480abda221\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWindow stays clamped like before.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2664+g256811a617",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Well it is documented to clamp the height just while the cmdline is expanded for messages. When a new command is entered it is ignored because it grows in height for a very long command, as UI1 does. Could only clamp the message part and still always show a very long command in it's entirety, but straying from that to avoid confusion with this option is probably fine.",
